<HL>
   Business Brief -- Cincinnati Bell Inc.:
   Unit Buys Majority Stake
   In 2 Telemarketing Firms
</HL>
<DATE>
08/06/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   CSN WNEWS
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Cincinnati Bell Inc. said its marketing unit, Matrixx
Marketing Inc., acquired majority ownership of two
telemarketing agencies in Paris. The price was about $39
million.
   The two companies -- Phone Marketing Services S.A. (PMS)
and Syscall S.A.R.L. -- were acquired from Sysmark Group
S.A., also based in Paris.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Closely held Sysmark will retain a minority stake in the
companies. Jean Paul Devai, Sysmark chairman, will become a
director of Matrixx Marketing Europe and an executive
director of Matrixx Marketing Inc.
</TEXT>
